The paper proposes a new model based on deep neural networks for learning the representation of multivariate time series data. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of deconvolutional networks and symbolic aggregate approximation for feature extraction suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the visualization of time series as complex networks using Markov matrices suggests that the paper may also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE).
